Mental training methods are helpful strategies for becoming more bal&shy;anced.  These include:

**Thought stopping:**  
No self-defeating thoughts, such as: &quot;I'll never make it.&quot;

**Affirmations (affirmation exercises):**  
&quot;Today, it will work!&quot; 

**Positive phrasing of sentences:**  
**Not** &quot;Today, I will not be nervous at the meeting&quot;** but **&quot;I will be completely focused during the meeting. I have prepared well!&quot;

Regularly give praise and recognition and in doing so put someone &quot;on a pedestal&quot;!

As human beings, we all have a &quot;legiti&shy;mate right to be respected by our fel&shy;low men and in turn are obliged to do the same for everyone else&quot;  
(Immanuel Kant: Metaphysics of Morals, TL, Academy Edition Volume VI, 462).
